So right now with the scalability limitations of the ethereum network Stacktical is still trememdously faster and cheaper than traditional SLA Managements. And with sidechains and ethereum scalability upgrades they are confident to meet the requirements of the public, so no worries here

In our case, that would be incentivizing online service stakeholders: providers, employees, users, insurance companies and so on.  If we talk about "mass" adoption, we're talking about getting the product in the hands of users. For now, we are focusing on helping online service providers manage the expectations of their users using SLAs, but at some point, we will also empower users themselves with more capabilities by launching products that are more or less dedicated to them.

The Stacktical platform monitors the health of services or get that information from trustworthy sources. It continuously verifies that providers respect their commitment, and distributes DSLA tokens accordingly

Title: [ANN]⚡️ STACKTICAL (DSLA): EARN TOKENS WHEN ONLINE SERVICES GO DOWN 👨‍💻--❌--🌐
Body: Hello Secrypt@3,  Great question! If Stacktical ever experiences performance issues or downtime that will trigger the DSLA that we have in the blockchain, our users will automatically receive DSLA as the decentralised DSLA system is not affected by the Stacktical offchain infrastructure.

Author: SilverSurfer972
Title: [ANN]⚡️ STACKTICAL (DSLA): EARN TOKENS WHEN ONLINE SERVICES GO DOWN 👨‍💻--❌--🌐
Body: Thank you for your interest Swipherji!  That's exactly why the use of the blockchain is an essential part of our project. Each downtime or performance failures will automatically trigger a compensation programmed in the DSLA smart contract agreed upon beforehand between Stacktical and the provider. This way, we don't have to manually keep track of all the services you use nor the ones you use experiencing technical issues. The compensation in DSLA token will be set depending on various criterias such as the length or the regularity of the performance failure etc.

Body: Hello, thank you for your question. Our main competitors are traditional Service Level Management platforms such as ServiceNow and Service Desk softwares such as Jira Service Desk or Zendesk. Also since they aim at improving the reliability of systems, Application & Network Monitoring Management tools such as New Relic can also be seen as indirect competitors of our SLO definition product.  However, using the blockchain we have a first-mover advantage. Author: SilverSurfer972
Title: [ANN]⚡️ STACKTICAL (DSLA): EARN TOKENS WHEN ONLINE SERVICES GO DOWN 👨‍💻--❌--🌐
Body: By allocating a relatively important share of the total supply to a compensation reserve. Providers that were not able to acquire DSLA tokens during the Token Sale will be able to borrow the amount of tokens they need from that reserve, to stake a compensation pool and publish their Service Level Agreement. Stacktical is based on a circular economy which has an imperative of managing finite supplies of resources, tokens in our case. Our DSLA token has an utility on the Stacktical platform and will support its mission through these different recycling mechanisms. As a result in this model nothing can become waste, or rather, waste is used to build capital instead of reducing it.

Body: A SLA (Service Level Agreement) is a contract that sets the quality of service a customer can expect from his online service provider (streaming, game, exchange...) and fair ways to settle disputes when the agreed quality is not met. In a nutshell, in the event of a technical failure such SLA would deemed violated and would automatically triggers the distribution of our DSLA through our platform.

Title: [ANN]⚡️ STACKTICAL (DSLA): EARN TOKENS WHEN ONLINE SERVICES GO DOWN 👨‍💻--❌--🌐
Body: Great comment! It is ! On supply chain SLAs, failure to deliver shipment A on time would trigger an automatic compensation to the receiver from the shipping provider according to the SLO terms.  For example those SLO: * >= 24 hours late delivery 10% refund of the shipment cost * >= 72 hours late delivery 45% refund of the shipment cost ...  SLAs are always capped to the service costs so often (cost of failure < cost of compensation) that's why using SLAs are Smart Contract is great because SLAs can be "linked" to traditional insurance via out crowdfundable smart contracts

Author: SilverSurfer972
Title: [ANN]⚡️ STACKTICAL (DSLA): EARN TOKENS WHEN ONLINE SERVICES GO DOWN 👨‍💻--❌--🌐
Body: Decentralized Service Level Agreements makes downtime compensation automatic. Because SLA enforcement and claims processes are painful and involves users contacting customer support it is a huge leap in customer service. By making SLA guarantees cheaper and easier to manage, service providers can offer better guarantees to every type of customers. Customer Service as we know is about to get much better and fair!

Body: Update  We are starting a experiment called Decentralized Café  Decentralized Café is a Daily Scrum Meeting format we are currently experimenting.  The Daily Scrum Meeting is a short everyday meeting that generally happens at the start of the working day. But because Stacktical is a globally-distributed team that is always on the go, not everybody is always able to attend this rendez-vous.  With Decentralized Café, our daily stand-up becomes asynchronous, multi media and transparently shared with the community. Anybody can catch up anytime with what their teammates have been up to (and now you can too).  To push the idea further, the traditional three question structure of the daily stand-up will be introduced by a short story connected to one of the daily items.  For feedbacks about Decentralized Café, please reach out on Telegram at https://t.me/stacktical

Author: SilverSurfer972
Title: [ANN]⚡️ STACKTICAL (DSLA): EARN TOKENS WHEN ONLINE SERVICES GO DOWN 👨‍💻--❌--🌐
Body: Website | White Paper | One Pager | Telegram | Medium | Twitter | Instagram | Facebook | Reddit | LinkedIn | Github    MEET DSLA, THE DOWNTIME COMPENSATION TOKEN  Stacktical helps providers showcase the reliability of their online services and automatically indemnify consumers when services do not work as expected. The platform relies on a circular economy, powered by the Decentralized Service Level Agreement (DSLA) ERC-20 utility token, as per the diagram below :    The provider defines service level objectives (A) and stake DSLA tokens (B) to form a compensation pool (C).  The compensation pool is depleted according to good service levels (D) and bad service levels (D’).  Token owners can either withdraw the DSLA they received as a compensation to their ERC-20 compatible wallet (E) or exchange them for promotional offers, loots and other service collectibles in the Stacktical marketplace (F).  All tokens exchanged on the Stacktical marketplace return to the compensation pool (C), ready to handle the next performance failure.  BENEFITS  For service providers:  Streamline their service level management process Streamline their (total) compensation management process Increase their attractivity as a service provider with demonstrable proofs of care Increase the reliability of their online services Increase the performance of their support teams Better retain consumers, customers and partners Better retain talent and support heroes Reduce the cost of disputes  For users:  Get automatically compensated upon performance failures and downtimes Access an exclusive catalog of service collectibles and loots Fair, Inclusive, Accountable, Transparent & Trustable service providers  For employees:  Get automatically compensation for proactively anticipating performance failures, meeting service level objectives and support objectives Increased employee satisfaction Increased service level management efficiency  TOKEN SALE  The DSLA private sale is in progress. The DSLA pre sale will start on November 1st 2018. The DSLA public sale date will be announced right after the end of the pre sale.  MORE INFORMATION  Fore more information about the Stacktical platform and the DSLA token sale, please read our white paper, one pager and visit our website at https://stacktical.com  Also make sure to join our Telegram if you have any question.  ABOUT STACKTICAL  Stacktical is a french software company specialized in applying predictive and blockchain technologies to performance, employee and customer management practices.  FIND US ELSEWHERE  Telegram Twitter Reddit Instagram Facebook Medium Github  BOUNTY PROGRAM https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=4696580  ANN TRANSLATIONS  JP: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=5043349.0 KO: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=4958792.0 FR: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=4754165.0 RU: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=4718766.0 DE: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=4969308.0 ES: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=5040691.0 PT: https://bitcointalk.org/index.php?topic=5037035.0
